 affects different measures of residential segregation by income.
 Table 2 measures residential segregation of households by household income
 level.
 Table 3 measures residential segregation of households by the ratio of
 household income to poverty threshold.
 Information theory index measures of segregation can range from zero under
 no segregation to one under complete segregation.
 Each table displays results of both OLS (odd columns) and IV (even columns)
