 Standardized point estimates for WRLURI attenuate almost proportionally
 up to the 4000m spatial scale.
 IV estimates roughly tripled the OLS coefficient estimate magnitudes.
 The IV is strong (
\begin_inset Formula $F=18.7$
\end_inset

), underidentification is rejected, and the null of exogenous instruments
